isValidState(android.net.wifi.Supplicant.Description: Returns true if the supplicant state is valid and false otherwise.

ClassDesc: From defs.h in wpa_supplicant. These enumeration values are used to indicate the current wpa_supplicant state. This is more fine-grained than most users will be interested in. In general, it is better to use @B_android#net#NetworkInfo#State_E@. Note, the order of these enum constants must match the numerical values of the state constants in defs.h in wpa_supplicant.
